            "widgets_values": [
              "low-poly dirty indie game concept art, PS1 aesthetic, harsh geometry, analog noise\n\ninterior of a large house entrance or hallway, slightly damaged, grounded environment\n\nwide shot, static camera, framing all characters in the same space\n\nthe protagonist stands holding a small girl by the hand, positioned between her and a group of armed police officers\n\nthe girl looks fragile, small, slightly behind the protagonist, body tense, not crying but close to breaking\n\nthe protagonist is tired, tense, but not aggressive, posture defensive rather than attacking\n\npolice officers aim weapons, maintaining distance, rigid formation\n\nimportant: no one is moving — frozen moment of decision\n\nlighting is dim and realistic, slightly cold, no dramatic highlights\n\ncolors muted and grounded\n\nsubtle details: signs of recent violence in the environment (disturbed furniture, traces of damage), but not the focus\n\ntone: extreme tension, moral conflict, fragile balance, silence before decision\n\nno action, no shooting\nno dynamic poses\nno cinematic hero framing\nno exaggerated emotions or screaming\nno horror elements\nno stylization"
            ]
          }
